WEBVTT

00:45.312 --> 00:48.247
[dramatic piano music]

00:48.249 --> 00:55.421
♪ ♪

01:01.996 --> 01:04.630
<i> - I guess someone</i>
<i> has to be the monster.</i>

01:07.468 --> 01:11.537
<i> The one who favors reason</i>
<i> and shatters dreams.</i>

01:14.742 --> 01:16.875
<i> I've died and sacrificed</i>
<i> my bond with Alex</i>

01:16.877 --> 01:18.711
<i> so many times for this train.</i>

01:20.547 --> 01:23.216
<i> To surrender now would</i>
<i> render that meaningless.</i>

01:24.551 --> 01:28.553
<i> So maybe it was inevitable</i>
<i> that the monster would be me.</i>

01:28.689 --> 01:31.490
[indistinct chatter]

01:31.626 --> 01:34.559
- All right, we hold here!
Stay ready!

01:34.695 --> 01:35.895
If there's any trouble today,

01:36.030 --> 01:38.497
our job is to keep
the factions apart.

01:39.434 --> 01:41.634
- Look, Melanie dropped a bomb.

01:41.769 --> 01:43.436
Whether the Tail
will fight for New Eden now--

01:43.571 --> 01:45.504
- Whether they'll fight for me.

01:45.640 --> 01:48.708
- Well, we'll see.

01:51.512 --> 01:53.846
- Back in the fatigues, I see.

01:53.981 --> 01:56.048
- I wish that weren't
a good name for them.

01:57.518 --> 02:00.586
Hey, you ready for this?

02:00.721 --> 02:02.187
Being the bad guys?

02:02.189 --> 02:04.056
- If the passengers feel
anything like I do

02:04.191 --> 02:05.791
about being lied to,

02:05.926 --> 02:07.260
we're not the bad guys.

02:07.394 --> 02:11.197
Layton, Ben, the New Eden team,
those guys are.

02:14.535 --> 02:15.734
And Wilford?

02:15.736 --> 02:17.936
- Still missing.

02:17.938 --> 02:19.538
- Well, that's a problem.

02:19.540 --> 02:24.944
♪ ♪

02:25.079 --> 02:27.346
- [panting]

02:27.482 --> 02:33.218
♪ ♪

02:33.220 --> 02:36.088
What are you doing?
- [gasps]

02:36.223 --> 02:37.422
Trespassing.

02:37.424 --> 02:39.525
- Well, if you're here,
the dam is breaking.

02:40.628 --> 02:42.561
- What dam?

02:42.563 --> 02:43.696
Melanie and Layton?

02:43.831 --> 02:45.998
- No. Wilford.

02:47.368 --> 02:49.034
<i> Whatever you're up to</i>
<i> with him,</i>

02:49.036 --> 02:50.903
I don't want any part of it.

02:51.038 --> 02:53.839
- John, I'm not
on that side anymore.

02:53.841 --> 02:55.508
John! Stop.

02:55.643 --> 02:57.576
It's not like that.
You can trust me.

02:57.712 --> 03:00.445
- "John" now, is it?
- Clear! Just these two.

03:00.581 --> 03:01.646
- All right, move in!

03:01.648 --> 03:03.115
- He's here.

03:04.251 --> 03:06.451
- Go! Go! Go!

03:06.453 --> 03:09.454
[dramatic piano music]

03:09.456 --> 03:11.056
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

03:11.058 --> 03:12.992
- We're gonna set up
right here!

03:12.994 --> 03:15.594
[indistinct chatter]

03:15.730 --> 03:17.663
- Get up. Get up. Let's go.

03:17.798 --> 03:24.904
♪ ♪

03:26.341 --> 03:29.208
<i> [ominous music]</i>

03:29.344 --> 03:30.275
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

03:30.411 --> 03:32.811
<i> - The original sinners,</i>

03:32.813 --> 03:35.480
<i> me and Melanie.</i>

03:35.482 --> 03:38.684
<i> I should've known</i>
<i> it would come down to this.</i>

03:38.686 --> 03:43.422
<i> How else would we choose</i>
<i> humanity's fate but by war...</i>

03:43.424 --> 03:48.627
<i> both: On Snowpiercer,</i>
<i> 1029 cars long?</i>

03:48.763 --> 03:51.630
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

03:51.766 --> 03:58.905
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

04:07.582 --> 04:08.647
[piano plays off-key]

04:08.649 --> 04:09.815
- Oh--

04:12.053 --> 04:15.321
- It's time, darling.
I'm making my move.

04:17.124 --> 04:19.058
I would ravish you
here and now,

04:19.060 --> 04:22.595
but you understand.

04:22.730 --> 04:24.397
- Sure.

04:26.133 --> 04:28.000
- We're fighting
from the bottom.

04:28.135 --> 04:29.936
I've got to be smart!

04:31.538 --> 04:35.274
We'll set up shop right here
between the two camps.

04:35.410 --> 04:37.877
A fine vantage.

04:38.012 --> 04:40.679
Dr. Headwood! Where's our boy?

04:40.815 --> 04:42.281
- Right here, sir.

04:42.417 --> 04:45.218
- There he is! Yes!

04:45.352 --> 04:47.420
Hello, lad.

04:47.554 --> 04:49.888
Our new Coldman,

04:49.890 --> 04:52.958
rescued from
the aquarium explosion,

04:53.094 --> 04:55.560
resurrected by the good doctor.

04:55.562 --> 04:56.629
What do you think?

04:56.764 --> 04:59.564
[cheers and applause]

04:59.566 --> 05:00.833
Icy Boki!

05:00.968 --> 05:02.435
- Yeah!
- Whoo!

05:02.570 --> 05:04.036
- Boki!

05:04.171 --> 05:07.240
[all chanting]
Boki! Boki! Boki! Boki! Boki!

05:09.510 --> 05:11.310
- Obviously, I would love

05:11.446 --> 05:14.313
to have your support
with Hospitality.

05:14.315 --> 05:15.581
- Obviously.

05:15.716 --> 05:16.782
- And I'm hoping
you can tell me

05:16.784 --> 05:18.183
where Alex is right now.

05:18.185 --> 05:20.719
- She's probably
with Mr. Layton.

05:20.855 --> 05:22.922
You've shattered
her dreams too.

05:26.193 --> 05:30.195
We were going to New Eden
in your honor,

05:30.331 --> 05:32.465
completing your mission.
- No.

05:32.599 --> 05:35.268
My mission is to ensure
our survival on this train

05:35.402 --> 05:37.403
until we know
it's safe to get off.

05:39.073 --> 05:41.207
Will you help me
complete that mission?

05:43.077 --> 05:45.978
Help me serve the passengers
like you always have.

05:47.948 --> 05:49.215
Please.

05:52.820 --> 05:54.287
- Any more on Wilford?

05:54.421 --> 05:56.889
- Escaped and unaccounted for.
Javi's still not picking up,

05:57.024 --> 05:58.757
so I haven't been able
to yell at him yet.

05:58.759 --> 06:00.225
- That's not gonna help.

06:00.361 --> 06:02.761
- She's probably right.
How long till the turn?

06:02.763 --> 06:03.896
- 24 hours.

06:04.031 --> 06:05.230
I don't wanna drop anchor yet,

06:05.232 --> 06:07.366
but I can slow us down.

06:07.368 --> 06:09.168
- Hey. I need you.

06:09.170 --> 06:11.304
- Any news on where Alex is?
- No word.

06:11.438 --> 06:12.972
- Hey, slow down just enough
to piss them off.

06:13.107 --> 06:14.373
Make Javi call us.

06:14.509 --> 06:15.708
- On it.
- How bad is it?

06:15.843 --> 06:17.376
- New Eden still has support,

06:17.378 --> 06:19.578
but anyone who was on the fence
is backing Melanie.

06:19.580 --> 06:21.580
- Ag-Sec voted.

06:21.716 --> 06:22.915
They want the train.

06:23.050 --> 06:24.583
- Ag-Sec. Jesus Christ.
- Yeah.

06:24.585 --> 06:27.186
Well, maybe if the messaging
off the top wasn't a lie.

06:27.188 --> 06:29.989
- Hey. The science
still merits the risk.

06:29.991 --> 06:31.390
- Yeah, I know.
- See?

06:31.392 --> 06:32.591
- Let's go.

06:32.593 --> 06:35.594
<i> [tense music]</i>

06:35.596 --> 06:37.863
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

06:37.865 --> 06:39.332
- Hey.

06:39.466 --> 06:41.334
- So?

06:41.468 --> 06:42.935
- I don't know.

06:43.070 --> 06:44.770
You better hear them out.

06:50.811 --> 06:52.011
Hey.

06:52.146 --> 06:55.814
[indistinct chatter]

06:55.816 --> 06:57.282
- Thank you for coming.

06:57.284 --> 07:00.019
- Yo, Lay, the Tail
came for answers, man.

07:00.154 --> 07:02.487
- Hey, New Eden was a lie,
mate! We know it!

07:02.489 --> 07:04.089
- Liar!
I don't wanna hear anything--

07:04.091 --> 07:05.758
- The lie is on me. It is.

07:05.893 --> 07:10.363
I used dirty politics to try
and bring the train together.

07:10.497 --> 07:13.498
But--hey, but!
Don't let that overshadow

07:13.634 --> 07:17.102
what the Engineers
have showed us is possible.

07:17.104 --> 07:18.437
- How possible are we
really talking this time?

07:18.573 --> 07:19.838
- Yeah.

07:19.840 --> 07:21.240
- Can you get us
off this train or not?

07:21.242 --> 07:22.641
[indistinct chatter]

07:22.777 --> 07:25.044
- With you, I can get us there.

07:25.046 --> 07:26.645
I can't promise you

07:26.781 --> 07:30.049
that New Eden
can support life long-term.

07:30.051 --> 07:33.118
Hey, but the Tail knows

07:33.120 --> 07:34.921
neither can this train.

07:36.190 --> 07:39.191
We've suffered
under Melanie's rule before.

07:39.326 --> 07:41.594
We can't go back to that.

07:41.729 --> 07:44.263
<i> [stirring music]</i>

07:44.399 --> 07:47.132
- I don't know.
Can we can trust him again?

07:47.134 --> 07:48.934
- Let's get it done then.

07:49.070 --> 07:51.536
[cheering]
- To New Eden!

07:51.538 --> 07:52.805
all: New Eden!

07:52.940 --> 07:54.307
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

07:56.077 --> 07:57.844
- You've got a visitor.

07:58.946 --> 08:01.480
- Mr. Roche.

08:01.482 --> 08:02.682
Good to see you.

08:03.951 --> 08:06.819
Our relationship is so
stimulating now it's personal.

08:06.954 --> 08:09.154
- Yeah, I do take murder
personally, sir.

08:09.156 --> 08:11.356
Just added three of my brakemen
to the list.

08:11.492 --> 08:12.958
- [sighs]

08:13.094 --> 08:14.627
I'm sorry about that.

08:14.762 --> 08:17.696
They'll be the last bodies
of this affair from me.

08:17.698 --> 08:19.164
Some deterrence.

08:19.166 --> 08:21.567
<i> [tense music]</i>

08:21.702 --> 08:23.502
- Breachman Boscovic.
Looking good.

08:23.638 --> 08:25.971
- Yes. We don't want anyone
coming in here unannounced.

08:26.107 --> 08:28.173
Do we, Boki?
Apart from that,

08:28.309 --> 08:31.376
I'm just here to help you
keep the two sides apart.

08:31.378 --> 08:33.178
- All right, everyone,
listen up.

08:33.180 --> 08:34.780
If anybody is here
against their will,

08:34.915 --> 08:38.583
anybody who wants to leave,
they can, with me, right now.

08:38.585 --> 08:40.719
[laughter]

08:40.721 --> 08:42.054
- Audrey?

08:42.189 --> 08:44.924
- I'm out.
- Oz, where are you going?

08:48.062 --> 08:49.528
I'm not going with him.

08:49.664 --> 08:51.063
- Good. Good.

08:51.198 --> 08:55.935
Boki, why don't you
show Mr. Osweiller out?

08:56.070 --> 08:59.305
[both grunting]

09:01.608 --> 09:03.142
[laughter]

09:03.278 --> 09:06.279
- Come on. Get up. Get up.
Get up.

09:06.413 --> 09:08.213
- [roars]
- Let's go. Come on!

09:08.215 --> 09:09.815
- Go, Boki.

09:09.817 --> 09:12.417
[all cheering]

09:12.553 --> 09:14.287
Yeah, Bokes!

09:14.421 --> 09:16.088
[laughing]

09:16.223 --> 09:18.291
- [growling]

09:21.028 --> 09:23.196
- Just go easy on her,
all right?

09:25.366 --> 09:27.032
- I heard stories about you,

09:27.168 --> 09:28.501
about how ruthless
you could be.

09:28.635 --> 09:30.569
- Can we sit?
- Congratulations, Mom.

09:30.705 --> 09:32.237
Who knew you would make
your move

09:32.373 --> 09:34.173
literally
right after we saved you?

09:34.175 --> 09:36.976
- We have to look at it
objectively.

09:36.978 --> 09:38.243
If you can't do that,

09:38.379 --> 09:39.778
you've lost your way
as an Engineer.

09:39.780 --> 09:41.514
- Melanie, don't.

09:41.648 --> 09:43.248
- All I need you to do
is speak to Layton

09:43.384 --> 09:44.850
before this goes any further.

09:44.986 --> 09:47.853
<i> [tense music]</i>

09:47.989 --> 09:48.988
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

09:48.990 --> 09:52.158
[metal screeching]

10:06.607 --> 10:08.207
- Thank you for meeting
with me.

10:08.209 --> 10:10.275
- I appreciate the opportunity
to discuss facts.

10:10.411 --> 10:12.211
- The fact is,
most of us accept the risk.

10:12.347 --> 10:14.880
- You never disclosed
the risks.

10:14.882 --> 10:17.016
You're putting all our eggs
in one basket.

10:17.151 --> 10:18.483
The track is not tested.

10:18.485 --> 10:19.685
- Melanie, take the turn,

10:19.820 --> 10:22.355
or the Tail army
will do it for you.

10:22.489 --> 10:24.690
- Really?

10:24.692 --> 10:27.492
We both know it's a long march
to the Engine.

10:27.494 --> 10:30.295
- You don't have the forces
to defend.

10:30.297 --> 10:32.031
- I can hold you off
long enough.

10:32.033 --> 10:33.298
- And then what?

10:33.434 --> 10:35.634
Endless seesaw battles
for control?

10:35.636 --> 10:37.370
- No. We wait!

10:37.504 --> 10:39.705
We just wait
until we know we're right.

10:39.707 --> 10:42.441
- Don't do that, Mom.
Change course.

10:42.577 --> 10:44.177
The young people wanna get off.

10:44.311 --> 10:46.312
- How can I let you
if it's not safe?

10:49.116 --> 10:51.184
I want you with me.

10:51.318 --> 10:53.252
- Then you'll have
to take the turn.

10:53.388 --> 10:59.725
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

10:59.727 --> 11:02.327
- Oh, come on!
For pity's sake, both of you!

11:02.329 --> 11:03.796
- In or out, Ruth?

11:03.931 --> 11:05.264
- Well, I'm not letting you go
on your own, am I?

11:05.400 --> 11:06.799
Hey, this isn't over.

11:06.934 --> 11:08.467
Figure something out.

11:13.941 --> 11:16.075
- Now we gotta make a move.

11:22.850 --> 11:25.451
[indistinct chatter]

11:25.586 --> 11:26.919
- Here we go!
Here we go!

11:27.054 --> 11:28.187
- How far are we going?

11:28.322 --> 11:29.855
- Keep going
till we control Ag-Sec.

11:29.991 --> 11:32.558
- It's the food supply.
We need the seed bank.

11:34.996 --> 11:37.329
- Get out of the way!

11:37.331 --> 11:39.131
- Keep it rolling.
- Move! Move! Move!

11:39.133 --> 11:40.733
Coming through!

11:42.136 --> 11:44.870
[alarms blaring]

11:44.872 --> 11:46.938
- Ben, why are we slowing?

11:46.940 --> 11:48.608
- I'm not braking, Javi.

11:48.742 --> 11:51.410
- You lie like a rug.
I can see it.

11:51.545 --> 11:53.212
- That's just
a little resistance.

11:53.347 --> 11:55.381
Here, have some more.

11:57.951 --> 11:59.751
- Hey, Ben?

11:59.887 --> 12:02.154
Do you mind looking
after Liana for a minute?

12:02.156 --> 12:03.656
I won't be long.

12:05.359 --> 12:07.660
- Uh, well...

12:16.638 --> 12:17.969
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

12:17.971 --> 12:19.571
- Come on, move!

12:19.707 --> 12:21.106
Out of the way!

12:21.108 --> 12:23.242
- Y'all trying to face down
a army with a garden hose?

12:23.377 --> 12:24.976
- Out of the way!

12:24.978 --> 12:26.378
- Go, go, go!
- Go, run!

12:26.380 --> 12:27.847
- This is the last
greenhouse, Layton!

12:27.981 --> 12:30.382
- Tailies!
Set up the front line here!

12:30.518 --> 12:31.851
- Go! Go! Go!
- Out of the way!

12:31.985 --> 12:33.385
Out of the way!

12:33.387 --> 12:35.787
- Hey, we could keep on going.
- No! No, no, no.

12:35.923 --> 12:38.257
If we trigger the first clash,
it's all on us.

12:38.392 --> 12:40.792
- Agreed. Have we heard
from our forces uptrain?

12:40.794 --> 12:41.727
- Yeah, yeah.

12:41.863 --> 12:43.128
They're hiding and ready
if we need them.

12:43.130 --> 12:44.530
- We'll need them.

12:44.666 --> 12:47.333
- [panting]

12:47.468 --> 12:49.669
Back off! I got information!

12:49.803 --> 12:51.270
Bess! Bess!

12:51.405 --> 12:53.372
- Let him through! Move!

12:55.209 --> 12:57.343
- Wilford took the Nightcar.

12:57.345 --> 13:00.412
He's in there with
about a dozen guys and Boki.

13:00.414 --> 13:01.613
- Boki's alive?

13:01.749 --> 13:04.016
- Yeah, well,
if you can call it that.

13:04.018 --> 13:05.284
He's his new Coldman.

13:05.419 --> 13:07.353
- What?
- Audrey's in there too.

13:07.488 --> 13:10.356
- What? Against her will?
- I don't know.

13:10.358 --> 13:11.823
She didn't leave
when she had the chance.

13:11.959 --> 13:13.759
- Of course she didn't.
Together again, right?

13:13.761 --> 13:16.428
- No. No, she's not
on Wilford's side.

13:16.564 --> 13:18.030
- Something you're not
telling me?

13:18.032 --> 13:20.966
- She's not going back to him.
She can't.

13:20.968 --> 13:22.434
- Psst!

13:22.436 --> 13:25.371
My whistle is wanting,
and so is the help.

13:29.377 --> 13:31.176
You think this is your room?

13:31.312 --> 13:33.379
I am the Nightcar.

13:33.514 --> 13:35.114
- Have you missed court,
Audrey?

13:36.450 --> 13:40.052
- Sir, Zarah is waiting
for you in the back room.

13:40.054 --> 13:41.354
- All right.
- No one is safe.

13:47.261 --> 13:50.596
- Zarah. [chuckles]

13:50.732 --> 13:53.599
Hmm, vipers' nest out there.

13:53.601 --> 13:57.336
- Just how you like it, Joseph.
You'll be fanning the flames

13:57.471 --> 13:59.572
until you're
the last one standing.

14:00.742 --> 14:02.808
- How can I help?

14:02.810 --> 14:05.778
- I wanna make sure that
our arrangement still stands.

14:07.348 --> 14:08.748
That my daughter will be safe

14:08.882 --> 14:10.816
no matter how
this all plays out.

14:10.818 --> 14:12.218
- Of course.

14:12.353 --> 14:16.689
I intend to honor
our agreement, as do you.

14:20.561 --> 14:23.162
- Layton took Ag-Sec
without firing a shot.

14:23.297 --> 14:25.230
His people stuck with him.

14:25.232 --> 14:27.433
He holds all the cards now,
Melanie.

14:27.568 --> 14:29.301
- Can the Brakemen hold him?

14:29.437 --> 14:31.103
- Roche won't fight your war.

14:31.238 --> 14:33.172
He serves the people.

14:33.307 --> 14:35.641
You don't have the pull
you once did, you know.

14:37.244 --> 14:38.344
- [scoffs]

14:40.181 --> 14:42.848
[sighs]

14:42.984 --> 14:44.617
I need an ally.

14:46.454 --> 14:48.520
- Not Wilford.

14:48.522 --> 14:50.256
- I can control him.

14:50.391 --> 14:51.857
- That's not the point.

14:51.859 --> 14:54.326
- No, the point--

14:54.328 --> 14:56.929
the point is this,
it's everything.

14:58.266 --> 14:59.765
Every last soul on Earth.

15:02.403 --> 15:06.071
If I have to sell mine
to protect theirs,

15:06.207 --> 15:08.207
so be it, right?

15:11.278 --> 15:13.613
- Well, I'm sorry,
but I've spent

15:13.747 --> 15:16.282
too long redeeming myself
to go back now.

15:16.417 --> 15:19.285
<i> [tense music]</i>

15:19.420 --> 15:26.559
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

15:29.296 --> 15:31.230
- [grunts]
all: Oh!

15:31.365 --> 15:33.965
- Ow!
- That had to hurt!

15:33.967 --> 15:36.968
- The widow Headwood
upgraded a side effect.

15:36.970 --> 15:40.873
"Loss of sensation" is now
"impervious to pain."

15:42.776 --> 15:46.045
Our finest Breachman yet.
Ready for the field.

15:46.180 --> 15:48.648
No suit required.

15:48.782 --> 15:50.782
- Well, that's good.
Someone from Layton's side

15:50.918 --> 15:52.518
seems to have stolen
all the breach suits.

15:52.520 --> 15:55.254
- The problem is, Melanie,

15:55.389 --> 15:57.923
you're a legend.

15:57.925 --> 15:58.924
So you do have support--

15:59.060 --> 16:02.394
former Firsties,
some Guilds, et cetera--

16:02.396 --> 16:04.997
but you're both
militarily outmatched

16:05.132 --> 16:06.398
and down in the polls.

16:06.534 --> 16:08.400
So you need me.

16:08.402 --> 16:11.003
Two legends
are better than one.

16:11.005 --> 16:12.872
- I believe if we were seen
as united,

16:13.007 --> 16:15.074
then the majority of passengers
would choose the train, yes.

16:15.209 --> 16:16.676
- Well, of course.

16:16.810 --> 16:19.345
But it still comes down
to fear,

16:19.347 --> 16:20.946
fear of Layton's colony,

16:21.082 --> 16:23.015
or fear of the train
that got them this far.

16:23.150 --> 16:25.885
- There's only one way
that this works.

16:26.020 --> 16:27.953
- Here it comes.

16:27.955 --> 16:29.288
- I'm Head Engineer.

16:30.491 --> 16:32.792
And you retire
from Engineering altogether.

16:34.896 --> 16:36.629
It's my train.

16:45.907 --> 16:51.110
- Assuming generous comforts,
meaningful consultation,

16:51.245 --> 16:56.382
and if I maintained control
of certain interests of mine--

16:56.517 --> 16:57.917
cold treatment for example--

16:58.052 --> 17:01.721
- Assuming all of that
and all of my shame

17:01.855 --> 17:04.256
of cutting a deal with you,
if that helps.

17:04.392 --> 17:07.259
<i> [tense music]</i>

17:07.395 --> 17:10.062
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

17:10.197 --> 17:11.530
- Yes.

17:11.665 --> 17:14.533
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

17:14.668 --> 17:15.935
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

17:16.070 --> 17:18.871
[crowd cheering]

17:25.646 --> 17:28.514
<i> [tense music]</i>

17:28.649 --> 17:35.721
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

17:40.461 --> 17:42.128
- Resistance.

17:42.263 --> 17:43.329
- Ruth?

17:43.464 --> 17:45.731
- Lights?

17:45.866 --> 17:47.466
You all on your own here?

17:47.601 --> 17:49.535
- Yeah.
What are you doing here?

17:49.670 --> 17:52.404
- I thought Layton would hide
a team up here.

17:52.540 --> 17:55.207
Right, well,
I guess it's just us then.

17:55.209 --> 17:57.009
- I stole all the breach suits.

17:57.011 --> 17:59.345
I'm waiting for more orders.
What's up out there?

17:59.480 --> 18:00.613
- I'll fill you in later.

18:00.748 --> 18:02.481
How are you communicating
with Layton?

18:02.483 --> 18:04.483
- Old-fashion way.

18:04.485 --> 18:06.618
- Oh, is that my
little rat friend?

18:06.620 --> 18:09.956
Hey. [kisses] Hey.

18:10.090 --> 18:11.991
Hiya. Hiya.

18:14.094 --> 18:15.828
- What a pair.

18:15.830 --> 18:17.630
- Together, we tip the scales.

18:17.632 --> 18:19.031
The hope being that Layton
won't go to war

18:19.167 --> 18:21.033
over New Eden
without a majority.

18:21.035 --> 18:24.036
- And you really think this
guy's gonna take a back seat?

18:24.038 --> 18:26.572
- You're out to pasture,
aren't you, Joseph?

18:26.707 --> 18:29.375
- More of a trusted advisor.

18:29.510 --> 18:31.844
- Oh, this is gonna be great.

18:31.980 --> 18:33.980
- So right now,
all I want is for you

18:34.114 --> 18:36.182
to take your men down there
and stand in his way.

18:36.316 --> 18:39.918
- Excellent first step.
Exactly my counsel.

18:40.054 --> 18:41.920
- The goal
is to prevent violence.

18:42.056 --> 18:44.723
Let's show Layton the power
has swung our way.

18:45.660 --> 18:48.394
- All right, folks,
we're on the move! Shields up!

18:48.529 --> 18:52.531
We are marching downtrain to
form up and prevent an advance.

18:52.533 --> 18:56.068
Let's go!
- Move! Move out! Let's go!

18:56.070 --> 18:59.071
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

18:59.073 --> 19:02.741
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

19:02.743 --> 19:05.344
- Brakemen! Brakemen coming!

19:05.479 --> 19:10.148
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

19:10.150 --> 19:11.417
- Roche picked a side.

19:11.552 --> 19:12.885
[alarm blaring]

19:13.021 --> 19:19.491
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

19:19.627 --> 19:24.063
- Layton, Melanie and Wilford
have joined forces against you.

19:25.499 --> 19:27.499
Look, I'm sorry,
it's just numbers, man.

19:27.635 --> 19:29.468
You don't have the mandate now.

19:31.372 --> 19:32.438
- Who's taking that poll?

19:32.573 --> 19:34.172
- They're voting
with their feet up here.

19:34.308 --> 19:36.108
You can't force them
to the promised land.

19:36.110 --> 19:39.445
- So you came to force us
back to the Tail?

19:39.580 --> 19:42.849
- Listen!
Discuss it amongst yourselves.

19:42.983 --> 19:44.783
You got two hours
to stand down.

19:44.785 --> 19:47.185
- No. We don't need two hours.

19:47.321 --> 19:51.057
Just ask your Brakemen if they
are really ready to do this!

19:51.191 --> 19:52.324
all: Yeah!

19:52.460 --> 19:55.527
[pounding]

19:55.529 --> 19:58.264
- All right, eyes front!
Eyes front!

19:58.399 --> 20:01.800
If you got a better idea,
hurry up with it!

20:01.802 --> 20:03.269
- Prepare to brace!

20:03.404 --> 20:05.471
We may not want blood,
but we're ready for it!

20:05.606 --> 20:08.274
- We learned every inch
of this track the hard way!

20:08.409 --> 20:12.344
And each one of us has earned
our passage off of this ark!

20:12.346 --> 20:14.613
all: Yeah!

20:14.615 --> 20:17.750
[crowd shouting]

20:31.499 --> 20:32.999
- Mel.

20:34.769 --> 20:36.435
- I made my choice
like you demanded.

20:36.437 --> 20:38.837
I left my friends to be here
in the Engine with you.

20:38.839 --> 20:40.306
Are you happy now?

20:40.441 --> 20:41.774
- No. I'm sorry.

20:41.776 --> 20:42.975
- I'm pretty sure
some of my friends

20:42.977 --> 20:44.310
are going to die tonight.

20:44.445 --> 20:49.081
- I don't want that.
Alex, I'm trying--Alex.

20:53.654 --> 20:55.988
- Got a message.

20:55.990 --> 20:58.257
Ruth's uptrain with Lights.
They're ready.

20:58.392 --> 20:59.658
- We can punch
through the Brakemen.

20:59.660 --> 21:01.393
- And then what?

21:01.395 --> 21:03.261
Half the people up there will
fight with Wilford and Melanie.

21:03.263 --> 21:05.264
- And the other half are there
against their will.

21:05.399 --> 21:07.065
- Like Audrey.

21:07.067 --> 21:09.802
- I'm not leaving her
over there, Layton.

21:09.804 --> 21:11.137
- The turn's coming up.

21:11.272 --> 21:13.405
We all know
there's gonna be a cost.

21:13.407 --> 21:16.175
- We have put these lives
on the line so many times.

21:17.411 --> 21:19.011
There has to be a better way.

21:21.682 --> 21:24.750
[phone ringing]

21:32.092 --> 21:34.493
- Getting close to the bell,
huh?

21:34.629 --> 21:37.163
- Yeah, it tolls for you too.

21:37.298 --> 21:42.300
Look, this isn't to surrender
or to bargain.

21:42.302 --> 21:43.636
It's just to acknowledge.

21:43.771 --> 21:45.704
- All right.

21:45.840 --> 21:47.439
Thanks for letting Alex
cross over.

21:47.441 --> 21:48.975
- It was her choice.

21:49.109 --> 21:51.644
And I knew
she'd be a double-edged sword.

21:51.779 --> 21:53.179
- Yeah.

21:53.313 --> 21:55.447
I'll probably lose her
by trying to save her.

21:55.583 --> 21:57.583
- Yeah, we've both got
enough ego to believe

21:57.718 --> 21:59.318
we can save everyone.

22:00.788 --> 22:04.056
We set ourselves up
in an impossible role.

22:04.192 --> 22:07.926
- Once you got the job,
it's so hard to let it go.

22:08.062 --> 22:10.596
- You really wanna let Wilford
be a part of that?

22:10.731 --> 22:13.799
<i> You're falling right back</i>
<i> into using fear to keep order.</i>

22:13.934 --> 22:15.934
- You picked up the sword.

22:15.936 --> 22:17.803
<i> Right back to shedding blood.</i>

22:20.608 --> 22:22.875
- Fear or blood?

22:24.612 --> 22:27.013
- And either way...

22:27.147 --> 22:28.614
he wins.

22:29.483 --> 22:31.217
- And we both lose.

22:34.154 --> 22:35.421
- What do you say, Icy Boki?

22:35.556 --> 22:36.955
[people cheering]

22:37.091 --> 22:39.358
Ready to go to downtrain
and have some fun?

22:39.493 --> 22:44.897
Come on, Audrey, how about
a song for the amassing troops?

22:46.767 --> 22:49.235
Come on.

22:49.370 --> 22:50.636
- I can't.

22:50.771 --> 22:53.039
I won't do it anymore.

22:53.173 --> 22:57.309
- Put your lovely fingers
back upon those keys.

22:57.311 --> 22:58.711
- Visitor, sir!

23:00.981 --> 23:03.249
- Can't wait
to get back to this.

23:04.452 --> 23:07.720
Ah! What's wrong, Melanie?

23:07.855 --> 23:10.723
Everything's going our way.

23:10.725 --> 23:14.793
- It's Layton.
He won't back down.

23:14.795 --> 23:16.929
- Well, he had his chance.

23:16.931 --> 23:18.397
- I'm not ordering an attack.

23:18.532 --> 23:20.533
- For God's sake,
rip off the band-aid!

23:20.668 --> 23:23.001
- It's my call.

23:23.003 --> 23:24.336
So if you want
to remain relevant,

23:24.338 --> 23:26.405
help me come up
with another solution.

23:26.540 --> 23:28.874
- Well, I might have
something up my sleeve.

23:29.009 --> 23:30.542
- Okay.

23:30.544 --> 23:33.479
- Less bloody,
but requiring dark maneuvers

23:33.614 --> 23:35.314
on a more personal scale.

23:36.284 --> 23:38.417
I may have access to something

23:38.552 --> 23:43.089
Layton will throw himself
into the volcano for.

23:43.892 --> 23:45.858
His daughter.

23:50.965 --> 23:53.065
- Straight out
of your playbook, huh?

23:54.502 --> 23:56.035
The enemy's child.

23:56.771 --> 23:59.972
- Sorry. It's a proven remedy.

24:00.108 --> 24:02.308
Just give me the word,
and I'll set it up.

24:02.443 --> 24:05.311
<i> [solemn music]</i>

24:05.446 --> 24:12.318
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

24:19.059 --> 24:21.260
- Hurry, Zarah.
The time is now.

24:24.933 --> 24:27.666
- One day, Melanie,
when I'm dead and gone,

24:27.668 --> 24:31.670
and you're an old woman
watching Alex at the helm,

24:31.672 --> 24:33.472
you'll thank me for this.

24:33.607 --> 24:35.208
- I sincerely hope so.

24:40.014 --> 24:41.413
- We're here, Joseph.

24:41.549 --> 24:43.749
- There she is. [laughs]

24:43.884 --> 24:46.218
Hello! How are you?

24:46.220 --> 24:48.487
You're all safe and sound.

24:48.622 --> 24:51.023
Everything you need
to force a surrender.

24:51.159 --> 24:52.891
[door buzzing]
- [roars]

24:52.893 --> 24:54.493
- Yeah, that's not
gonna happen.

24:54.629 --> 24:56.094
- [grunts]

24:56.230 --> 24:59.765
[breathing heavily]

24:59.900 --> 25:03.902
Oh, come on then, Iceman.
What you got, hey?

25:04.038 --> 25:06.372
- [panting]

25:06.507 --> 25:07.874
- Oh, shit.

25:08.977 --> 25:10.909
Oh, no, no, no, no, no. Oh.

25:11.045 --> 25:13.779
- [roaring]

25:13.914 --> 25:16.782
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

25:16.917 --> 25:18.384
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

25:18.519 --> 25:19.852
- Oh, oh.

25:20.989 --> 25:22.388
Come on, Boki.

25:22.523 --> 25:24.390
- Augh!

25:32.066 --> 25:34.600
- Very crafty.

25:34.735 --> 25:39.538
Are we all going
to work this out amicably then?

25:39.674 --> 25:40.806
- We are,

25:40.941 --> 25:42.842
only you're not coming
to the table.

25:47.281 --> 25:48.381
- Audrey.

25:53.287 --> 25:54.753
This was you,
wasn't it, Melanie?

25:54.889 --> 25:57.723
- Actually, Andre and I
came up with it together.

25:58.226 --> 26:00.026
I made it six months in here.

26:00.160 --> 26:02.895
There's suspension fluid.
Stimulant. Timer.

26:03.031 --> 26:04.363
You can only stay under so long

26:04.365 --> 26:06.164
before you have
to wake yourself up

26:06.300 --> 26:07.700
and figure out where you are.

26:07.835 --> 26:11.303
- You're too weak to simply
cut my throat, Layton.

26:11.439 --> 26:12.939
Cowards.

26:14.843 --> 26:16.542
All of you.

26:25.185 --> 26:26.519
- Goodbye, Joseph.

26:35.129 --> 26:37.330
- Everyone out.

26:38.999 --> 26:40.466
- Now, you old bastard,

26:40.601 --> 26:45.804
I reach down
and send you into hell.

26:45.806 --> 26:48.807
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

26:48.809 --> 26:55.948
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

26:57.285 --> 27:00.553
[beeping]

27:00.688 --> 27:07.627
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

27:24.512 --> 27:28.581
- Now we'll see
who's the real survivor.

27:28.716 --> 27:35.655
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

27:50.170 --> 27:52.238
- It's a good way forward.

27:53.107 --> 27:56.642
- The ones we love,
that'll be the cost.

27:59.580 --> 28:00.913
[chiming]

28:01.049 --> 28:03.249
Citizens of Snowpiercer,

28:03.384 --> 28:05.852
as the fork
to New Eden approaches,

28:05.986 --> 28:07.253
I am proud to say

28:07.388 --> 28:10.056
that we have found a way
through our impasse.

28:10.190 --> 28:14.526
<i> We agree the only course</i>
<i> is compromise,</i>

28:14.528 --> 28:18.330
and the answer
is individual choice.

28:18.332 --> 28:21.333
- The train
will be divided in Ag-Sec.

28:21.335 --> 28:23.736
<i> Every passenger</i>
<i> will be allowed to choose</i>

28:23.871 --> 28:28.941
between the train with me
and New Eden with Andre Layton.

28:28.943 --> 28:31.477
- Those who choose New Eden
need to understand

28:31.612 --> 28:34.012
<i> we don't know</i>
<i> what we'll find there.</i>

28:34.014 --> 28:35.414
<i> The journey will be dangerous.</i>

28:35.549 --> 28:38.384
<i> And, yes, it will require</i>
<i> a leap of faith.</i>

28:39.687 --> 28:45.291
But more importantly, desire
to build a new society.

28:46.094 --> 28:48.694
- Those of you who remain,

28:48.829 --> 28:50.096
<i> we know that life</i>

28:50.230 --> 28:52.698
<i> will continue to be hard</i>
<i> on Snowpiercer.</i>

28:52.833 --> 28:56.435
Bit by bit,
the train is breaking down.

28:56.570 --> 29:00.306
But we will no longer add to
that hardship with oppression.

29:00.441 --> 29:04.042
The train will run
on science and truth.

29:04.044 --> 29:08.647
And we will share the burden of
our limited resources together.

29:08.649 --> 29:11.650
<i> [stirring music]</i>

29:11.652 --> 29:13.652
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

29:13.654 --> 29:15.354
- Thank you.

29:16.724 --> 29:18.324
Whatever your choice,

29:18.459 --> 29:21.059
find hope and respect

29:21.061 --> 29:22.695
in your neighbor's fate.

29:23.998 --> 29:25.397
Talk to your families.

29:25.399 --> 29:27.333
Say goodbye to your friends.

29:27.468 --> 29:30.736
The train will separate
in just under six hours.

29:32.540 --> 29:34.473
[chiming]

29:42.951 --> 29:46.085
[indistinct chatter]

30:03.972 --> 30:05.605
- So...

30:07.107 --> 30:08.641
What do you wanna do?

30:11.646 --> 30:14.547
- I was the best version
of myself here.

30:15.850 --> 30:17.916
You showed me that.

30:18.052 --> 30:21.287
- Yeah, what was I thinking?

30:24.525 --> 30:26.258
- I have something
to give here,

30:26.394 --> 30:29.461
with art and who I am

30:29.463 --> 30:32.798
and how I can heal people
in my own way.

30:32.933 --> 30:35.201
I need to stay, Bess.

30:38.272 --> 30:40.539
- I...

30:40.675 --> 30:44.410
I've been dreaming to get
off this train for so long.

30:44.545 --> 30:45.944
- I know.

30:46.080 --> 30:50.116
- I can't see a life for me
on the Snowpiercer anymore.

30:52.553 --> 30:54.153
- Even if you loved me?

31:00.561 --> 31:02.428
- Even if I loved you.

31:02.563 --> 31:05.631
<i> [somber music]</i>

31:05.766 --> 31:10.236
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

31:10.371 --> 31:13.239
Oh, well.

31:13.374 --> 31:16.442
I'll see you before we break.

31:20.981 --> 31:23.182
[pounding on door]

31:28.122 --> 31:30.756
- Ah, shit. Come here.

31:32.660 --> 31:34.360
Come here.

31:40.401 --> 31:42.601
You want coffee?
- Yeah.

31:42.603 --> 31:43.936
What are you gonna do?

31:43.938 --> 31:45.171
- We're going.

31:48.342 --> 31:49.475
How about you?

31:49.610 --> 31:50.710
- I'm coming with you.

31:53.681 --> 31:55.881
- At least we'll be together.

31:56.016 --> 31:58.550
Anyway, I gave Carly
the choice.

31:58.552 --> 32:01.087
- I definitely want off.

32:01.221 --> 32:03.422
- So that's what we're doing.

32:03.557 --> 32:04.823
- Cheers, boss.

32:04.959 --> 32:06.526
- Cheers, Bess.

32:19.774 --> 32:22.208
- So how long do you think
she can keep going?

32:23.177 --> 32:24.577
- If you're lucky,

32:24.712 --> 32:28.847
you hop from crisis to crisis
for another decade.

32:28.849 --> 32:30.283
Maybe two.

32:32.586 --> 32:34.987
- I need you, Ben.

32:35.123 --> 32:36.722
- I needed you too.

32:37.592 --> 32:40.793
I followed your science
to the decision of getting off.

32:40.928 --> 32:43.329
You nearly killed it.
- It's still alive.

32:43.464 --> 32:45.598
It's just down the line.

32:45.733 --> 32:48.234
And if we're together,
I know we can get there.

32:50.271 --> 32:54.607
- I will serve with you
till the end of the world,

32:54.742 --> 32:56.142
but that's only half of it.

32:56.276 --> 32:58.911
You want me to stay?
I need the rest of you.

33:02.951 --> 33:04.217
- I'm here.

33:06.754 --> 33:08.421
I'm yours.

33:15.163 --> 33:17.497
- Well, then New Eden can wait.

33:24.639 --> 33:28.174
- Melanie and Ben are the best
Engineers there's ever been.

33:28.309 --> 33:29.976
I need to keep learning
with them.

33:30.110 --> 33:31.444
I'll be fine.

33:34.314 --> 33:36.315
- Okay.

33:36.450 --> 33:38.184
Hey, one Tail.

33:38.319 --> 33:41.920
- One Tail.
- One Tail.

33:41.922 --> 33:43.689
Always.

33:45.860 --> 33:47.793
Okay, no crying.

33:47.928 --> 33:49.662
I'll meet you at the breakpoint
to say goodbye.

33:49.664 --> 33:51.531
- Yeah.
- Come here.

33:57.071 --> 33:58.804
- I love you guys.

34:05.413 --> 34:12.552
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

34:18.759 --> 34:21.360
- That hurts.
- Yeah.

34:22.563 --> 34:25.831
Everyone's got
to choose their own path.

34:25.966 --> 34:27.700
- Yeah.

34:27.835 --> 34:30.002
It's all these pieces
left behind.

34:31.639 --> 34:33.505
- There are enough pieces left
for us

34:33.507 --> 34:35.474
to put ourselves back together.

34:38.046 --> 34:39.679
Are you with me?

34:46.054 --> 34:47.854
- Yeah, I'm with you.

34:47.988 --> 34:50.857
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

34:50.991 --> 34:55.528
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

34:59.400 --> 35:01.199
- Downtrain to New Eden.
Uptrain to stay.

35:01.335 --> 35:04.002
- Hello? Service?

35:04.004 --> 35:06.405
This part of the train
isn't stopping, you know.

35:12.346 --> 35:14.013
Well, he's a pilgrim now.

35:15.149 --> 35:17.049
- There's still time
to come with me, LJ.

35:18.819 --> 35:20.753
- You're chickening out,

35:20.755 --> 35:22.288
from me, from power,
and for what?

35:22.423 --> 35:23.822
To go plant potatoes
in an igloo?

35:23.824 --> 35:25.791
You don't even know.
- Yeah.

35:27.027 --> 35:28.027
I like that part.

35:35.235 --> 35:39.572
Goodbye, Lilah Junior
Folger-Osweiller.

35:41.642 --> 35:43.843
- Yeah, I'm gonna
drop the Osweiller!

35:46.246 --> 35:49.047
